‚úÖ 3. IInvokedMethodListener
üìå Use when: You want to perform actions before and after every method, including @BeforeMethod and @AfterMethod.

üéØ Example Use Case:

Log the name of each test and config method as they run.

Inject common headers/cookies before each test method execution.

@Override
public void beforeInvocation(IInvokedMethod method, ITestResult result) {
    if (method.isTestMethod()) {
        logStart(method.getTestMethod().getMethodName());
    }
}


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



package listeners;

import org.testng.IInvokedMethod;
import org.testng.IInvokedMethodListener;
import org.testng.ITestResult;

public class MyInvokedMethodListener implements IInvokedMethodListener {
    public void beforeInvocation(IInvokedMethod method, ITestResult result) {
        System.out.println("‚û°Ô∏è Before: " + method.getTestMethod().getMethodName());
    }
    public void afterInvocation(IInvokedMethod method, ITestResult result) {
        System.out.println("‚¨ÖÔ∏è After: " + method.getTestMethod().getMethodName());
    }
}
